      "date": "2018-05-12 03:23:29.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> I did that before and it lead to slab corruptions. The reason is\n > that the kobject layer itself does the freeing on release. If you\n > set it to NULL before the kobject calls its release routine that\n > will lead to attempting to kfree 0x00000000.\n\nI think there's some misunderstanding since nothing like that could happen with this patch, and I did plug it into my testing and don't see any problems yet (~10 hours ATM).\n\nThe reason is once we set our own pointer to NULL - we never call into kobject layer so we have zero chance of affecting actual kobject state (And the object is already freed here anyway).",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
